50|$|The Super 8, {{also sold}} {{under the title}} Tri-star or Tristar, is an {{unlicensed}} video <b>game</b> <b>peripheral</b> released in 1995 for the Super Nintendo Entertainment System designed to allow the system to run games developed for the Nintendo Entertainment System. The Super 8 utilized an NES-on-a-chip integrated circuit to duplicate the functionality of the original NES hardware, and connected to the SNES's own cartridge slot.|$|E
